configuration'\n            raise e\n\n    def post_validate(self, templar):\n        '''\n        Override of base class post_validate, to also do final validation on\n        the block and task include (if any) to which this task belongs.\n        '''\n\n        if self._parent:\n            self._parent.post_validate(templar)\n\n        if AnsibleCollectionConfig.default_collection:\n  Override post validation of vars on the play, as we don't want to\n        template these too early.\n        '''\n        env = {}\n        if value is not None:\n\n            def _parse_env_kv(k, v):\n                try:\n                    env[k] = templar.template(v, convert_bare=False)\n                except AnsibleUndefinedVariable as e:\n                    error = to_native(e)\n                    if self.action in C._ACTION_FACT_GATHERING and 'ansible_facts.env' in error or 'ansible_env' in error:\n                        # ignore as fact gathering is required for 'env' facts\n                        return\n                    raise\n\n            if isinstance(value, list):\n                for env_item in value:\n                    if isinstance(env_item, dict):\n                        for k in env_item:\n                            _parse_env_kv(k, env_item[k])\n                    else:\n                        isdict = templar.template(env_item, convert_bare=False)\n environment value, skipping: %s\" % value)\n\n            elif isinstance(value, dict):\n                # should not really happen\n                env = dict()\n                for env_item in value:\n                    _parse_env_kv(env_item, value[env_item])\n            else:\n                # at this point it should be a simple string, also should not happen\n                env = execution of the task is complete,\n        and should not be templated during the regular post_validate step.\n        '''\n        return value\n\n    def _post_validate_failed_when(self, attr,       return value\n\n    def _post_validate_until(self, attr, value, templar):\n        '''\n        until is evaluated after the execution of the task is complete,\n        and should not be all_vars['when']\n\n        return all_vars\n\n    def get_include_params(self):\n        all_vars = dict()\n        if self._parent:\n            all_vars.update(self._parent.get_include_params())\n        if self.action in C._ACTION_ALL_INCLUDES:\n            all_vars.update(self.vars)\n        return all_vars\n\n    def copy(self, exclude_parent=False, exclude_tasks=False):\n        new_me = super(Task, self).copy()\n\n        new_me._parent = None\n        if self._parent and not exclude_parent:\n            new_me._parent = self._parent.copy(exclude_tasks=exclude_tasks)\n\n        new_me._role = None\n        if self._role:\n            new_me._role = self._role\n\n        new_me.implicit = self.implicit\n        new_me.resolved_action = self.resolved_action\n\n        return new_me\n\n    def serialize(self):\n        data = super(Task, self).serialize()\n\n        if not self._squashed and not self._finalized:\n            if self._parent:\n                data['parent'] = self._parent.serialize()\n                data['parent_type'] = self._parent.__class__.__name__\n\n            if self._role:\n                data['role'] = self._role.serialize()\n\n            data['implicit'] = self.implicit\n            data['resolved_action'] = self.resolved_action\n\n        return data\n\n    def deserialize(self, data):\n\n        # import is here to avoid import loops\n        from ansible.playbook.task_include import TaskInclude\n        from ansible.playbook.handler_task_include import HandlerTaskInclude\n\n        parent_data = data.get('parent', None)\n        if parent_data:\n            parent_type = data.get('parent_type')\n            if parent_type == 'Block':\n                p = Block()\n            elif parent_type == 'TaskInclude':\n                p = TaskInclude()\n            elif parent_type == 'HandlerTaskInclude':\n                p = HandlerTaskInclude()\n            p.deserialize(parent_data)\n            self._parent = p\n            del data['parent']\n\n        role_data = data.get('role')\n        if role_data:\n            r = Role()\n            r.deserialize(role_data)\n            self._role = r\n            del data['role']\n\n        self.implicit = data.get('implicit', False)\n        self.resolved_action = data.get('resolved_action')\n\n        super(Task, self).deserialize(data)\n\n    def set_loader(self, loader):\n        '''\n        Sets the loader on this object and recursively on parent, child objects.\n        This is used primarily after the Task has been serialized/deserialized, which\n        does not preserve the loader.\n        '''\n\n        self._loader = loader\n\n        if self._parent:\n            self._parent.set_loader(loader)\n\n    def _get_parent_attribute(self, attr, extend=False, prepend=False):\n        '''\n        Generic logic to get the attribute or parent attribute for a task value.\n        '''\n\n        extend = self._valid_attrs[attr].extend\n        prepend = self._valid_attrs[attr].prepend\n        try:\n            value = self._attributes[attr]\n            # If parent is static, we can grab attrs from the parent\n            # otherwise, defer to the grandparent\n            if getattr(self._parent, 'statically_loaded', True):\n                _parent = self._parent\n            else:\n inheritable, other attributes might not be for the parent but still should be for other ancestors\n                    if attr != 'vars' and hasattr(_parent, '_get_parent_attribute'):\n                        parent_value = _parent._get_parent_attribute(attr)\n                    else:\n                        parent_value = _parent._attributes.get(attr, Sentinel)\n\n                    if extend:\n                        value = self._extend_value(value, parent_value, prepend)\n                    else:\n                        value = parent_value\n        except KeyError:\n            pass\n\n        return value\n\n    def all_parents_static(self):\n        if self._parent:\n            return self._parent.all_parents_static()\n        return True\n\n    def get_first_parent_include(self):\n        from ansible.playbook.task_include import TaskInclude\n        if self._parent:\n            if isinstance(self._parent, TaskInclude):\n                return k.replace(\"with_\", \"\") in lookup_loader:\n                # transform into loop property\n                self._preprocess_with_loop(ds, new_ds, k, v)\n            elif C.INVALID_TASK_ATTRIBUTE_FAILED or k in self._valid_attrs:\n                new_ds[k] = v\n            else:\n                display.warning(\"Ignoring invalid attribute: %s\" % k)\n\n        return super(Task, self).preprocess_data(new_ds)\n\n    def _load_loop_control(self, attr, ds):\n        if not isinstance(ds, dict):\n            raise AnsibleParserError(\n                \"the `loop_control` value must be specified as a dictionary and cannot \"\n                \"be a variable itself (though it can contain variables)\",\n                obj=ds,\n            )\n\n        return LoopControl.load(data=ds, variable_manager=self._variable_manager, loader=self._loader)\n\n    def _validate_attributes(self, ds):\n        try:\n            super(Task, self)._validate_attributes(ds)\n        except AnsibleParserError as e:\n            e.message += '\\nThis error can be suppressed as a warning using the \"invalid_task_attribute_failed\" configuration'\n            raise e\n\n    def post_validate(self, templar):\n        '''\n        Override of base class post_validate, to also do final validation on\n        the block and task include (if any) to which this task belongs.\n        '''\n\n        if self._parent:\n            self._parent.post_validate(templar)\n\n        if AnsibleCollectionConfig.default_collection:\n            pass\n\n        super(Task, self).post_validate(templar)\n\n    def _post_validate_loop(self, attr, value, templar):\n        '''\n        Override post validation for the loop field, which is templated\n        specially in the TaskExecutor class when evaluating loops.\n        '''\n        return value\n\n    def _post_validate_environment(self, attr, value, templar):\n        '''\n        Override post validation of vars on the play, as we don't want to\n        template these too early.\n        '''\n        env = {}\n        if value is not None:\n\n            def _parse_env_kv(k, v):\n                try:\n                    env[k] = templar.template(v, convert_bare=False)\n                except AnsibleUndefinedVariable as e:\n                    error = to_native(e)\n                    if self.action in C._ACTION_FACT_GATHERING and 'ansible_facts.env' in error or 'ansible_env' in error:\n                        # ignore as fact gathering is required for 'env' facts\n                        return\n                    raise\n\n            if isinstance(value, list):\n                for env_item in value:\n                    if isinstance(env_item, dict):\n                        for k in env_item:\n                            _parse_env_kv(k, env_item[k])\n                    else:\n                        isdict = templar.template(env_item, convert_bare=False)\n                        if isinstance(isdict, dict):\n                            env.update(isdict)\n                        else:\n                            display.warning(\"could not parse environment value, skipping: %s\" % value)\n\n            elif isinstance(value, dict):\n                # should not really happen\n                env = dict()\n                for env_item in value:\n                    _parse_env_kv(env_item, value[env_item])\n            else:\n                # at this point it should be a simple string, also should not happen\n                env = templar.template(value, convert_bare=False)\n\n        return env\n\n    def _post_validate_changed_when(self, attr, value, templar):\n        '''\n        changed_when is evaluated after the execution of the task is complete,\n        and should not be templated during the regular post_validate step.\n        '''\n        return value\n\n    def _post_validate_failed_when(self, attr, value, templar):\n        '''\n        failed_when is evaluated after the execution of the task is complete,\n        and should not be templated during the regular post_validate step.\n        '''\n        return value\n\n    def _post_validate_until(self, attr, value, templar):\n        '''\n        until is evaluated after the execution of the task is complete,\n        and should not be templated during the regular post_validate step.\n        '''\n        return value\n\n    def get_vars(self):\n        all_vars = dict()\n        if self._parent:\n            all_vars.update(self._parent.get_vars())\n\n        all_vars.update(self.vars)\n\n        if 'tags' in all_vars:\n            del all_vars['tags']\n        if 'when' in all_vars:\n            del all_vars['when']\n\n        return all_vars\n\n    def get_include_params(self):\n        all_vars = dict()\n        if self._parent:\n            all_vars.update(self._parent.get_include_params())\n        if self.action in C._ACTION_ALL_INCLUDES:\n            all_vars.update(self.vars)\n        return all_vars\n\n    def copy(self, exclude_parent=False, exclude_tasks=False):\n        new_me = super(Task, self).copy()\n\n        new_me._parent = None\n        if self._parent and not exclude_parent:\n            new_me._parent = self._parent.copy(exclude_tasks=exclude_tasks)\n\n        new_me._role = None\n        if self._role:\n            new_me._role = self._role\n\n        new_me.implicit = self.implicit\n        new_me.resolved_action = self.resolved_action\n\n        return new_me\n\n    def serialize(self):\n        data = super(Task, self).serialize()\n\n        if not self._squashed and not self._finalized:\n            if self._parent:\n                data['parent'] = self._parent.serialize()\n                data['parent_type'] = self._parent.__class__.__name__\n\n            if self._role:\n                data['role'] = self._role.serialize()\n\n            data['implicit'] = self.implicit\n            data['resolved_action'] = self.resolved_action\n\n        return data\n\n    def deserialize(self, data):\n\n        # import is here to avoid import loops\n        from ansible.playbook.task_include import TaskInclude\n        from ansible.playbook.handler_task_include import HandlerTaskInclude\n\n        parent_data = data.get('parent', None)\n        if parent_data:\n            parent_type = data.get('parent_type')\n            if parent_type == 'Block':\n                p = Block()\n            elif parent_type == 'TaskInclude':\n                p = TaskInclude()\n            elif parent_type == 'HandlerTaskInclude':\n                p = HandlerTaskInclude()\n            p.deserialize(parent_data)\n            self._parent = p\n            del data['parent']\n\n        role_data = data.get('role')\n        if role_data:\n            r = Role()\n            r.deserialize(role_data)\n            self._role = r\n            del data['role']\n\n        self.implicit = data.get('implicit', False)\n        self.resolved_action = data.get('resolved_action')\n\n        super(Task, self).deserialize(data)\n\n    def set_loader(self, loader):\n        '''\n        Sets the loader on this object and recursively on parent, child objects.\n        This is used primarily after the Task has been serialized/deserialized, which\n        does not preserve the loader.\n        '''\n\n        self._loader = loader\n\n        if self._parent:\n            self._parent.set_loader(loader)\n\n    def _get_parent_attribute(self, attr, extend=False, prepend=False):\n        '''\n        Generic logic to get the attribute or parent attribute for a task value.\n        '''\n\n        extend = self._valid_attrs[attr].extend\n        prepend = self._valid_attrs[attr].prepend\n        try:\n            value = self._attributes[attr]\n            # If parent is static, we can grab attrs from the parent\n            # otherwise, defer to the grandparent\n            if getattr(self._parent, 'statically_loaded', True):\n                _parent = self._parent\n            else:\n                _parent = self._parent._parent\n\n            if _parent and (value is Sentinel or extend):\n                if getattr(_parent, 'statically_loaded', True):\n                    # vars are always inheritable, other attributes might not be for the parent but still should be for other ancestors\n                    if attr != 'vars' and hasattr(_parent, '_get_parent_attribute'):\n                        parent_value = _parent._get_parent_attribute(attr)\n                    else:\n                        parent_value = _parent._attributes.get(attr, Sentinel)\n\n                    if extend:\n                        value = self._extend_value(value, parent_value, prepend)\n                    else:\n                        value = parent_value\n        except KeyError:\n            pass\n\n        return value\n\n    def all_parents_static(self):\n        if self._parent:\n            return self._parent.all_parents_static()\n        return True\n\n    def get_first_parent_include(self):\n        from ansible.playbook.task_include import TaskInclude\n        if self._parent:\n            if isinstance(self._parent, TaskInclude):\n                return self._parent\n            return self._parent.get_first_parent_include()\n        return None\n# Unit test for method get_include_params of class Task\ndef test_Task_get_include_params():"}], new_me._role = None\n        if self._role:\n            new_me._role = self._role\n\n        new_me.implicit = self.implicit\n        new_me.resolved_action = self.resolved_action\n\n        return new_me\n\n    def serialize(self):\n        data = super(Task, self).serialize()\n\n        if not self._squashed and not self._finalized:\n            if self._parent:\n                data['parent'] ds.get('vars'))\n        else:\n            new_ds['vars'] = dict()\n\n        for (k, v) in iteritems(ds):\n            if k in ('action', 'local_action', 'args', 'delegate_to') or k == action or k == 'shell':\n                # we don't want to re-assign these values, which were determined by the ModuleArgsParser() above\n                continue\n            elif k.startswith('with_') and k.replace(\"with_\", \"\") in lookup_loader:\n                # transform into loop property\n                self._preprocess_with_loop(ds, new_ds, k, v)\n            elif C.INVALID_TASK_ATTRIBUTE_FAILED or k in self._valid_attrs:\n                new_ds[k] = v\n            else:\n                display.warning(\"Ignoring invalid attribute: %s\" % k)\n\n        return super(Task, self).preprocess_data(new_ds)\n\n    def _load_loop_control(self, attr, ds):\n        if not isinstance(ds, dict):\n            raise AnsibleParserError(\n                \"the `loop_control` value must be specified as a dictionary and cannot \"\n                \"be a variable itself (though it can contain variables)\",\n                obj=ds,\n            )\n\n        return LoopControl.load(data=ds, variable_manager=self._variable_manager, loader=self._loader)\n\n    def _validate_attributes(self, ds):\n        try:\n            super(Task, self)._validate_attributes(ds)\n        except AnsibleParserError as e:\n            e.message += '\\nThis error can be suppressed as a warning using the \"invalid_task_attribute_failed\" configuration'\n            raise e\n\n    def post_validate(self, templar):\n        '''\n        Override of base class post_validate, to also do final validation on\n        the block and task include (if any) to which this task belongs.\n        '''\n\n        if self._parent:\n            self._parent.post_validate(templar)\n\n        if AnsibleCollectionConfig.default_collection:\n            pass\n\n        super(Task, self).post_validate(templar)\n\n    def _post_validate_loop(self, attr, value, templar):\n        '''\n        Override post validation for the loop field, which is templated\n        specially in the TaskExecutor class when evaluating loops.\n        '''\n        return value\n\n    def _post_validate_environment(self, attr, value, templar):\n        '''\n        Override post validation of vars on the play, as we don't want to\n        template these too early.\n        '''\n        env = {}\n        if value is not None:\n\n            def _parse_env_kv(k, v):\n                try:\n                    env[k] = templar.template(v, convert_bare=False)\n                except AnsibleUndefinedVariable as e:\n                    error = to_native(e)\n                    if self.action in C._ACTION_FACT_GATHERING and 'ansible_facts.env' in error or 'ansible_env' in error:\n                        # ignore as fact gathering is required for 'env' facts\n                        return\n                    raise\n\n            if isinstance(value, list):\n                for env_item in value:\n                    if isinstance(env_item, dict):\n                        for k in env_item:\n                            _parse_env_kv(k, env_item[k])\n                    else:\n                        isdict = templar.template(env_item, convert_bare=False)\n                        if isinstance(isdict, dict):\n                            env.update(isdict)\n                        else:\n                            display.warning(\"could not parse environment value, skipping: %s\" % value)\n\n            elif isinstance(value, dict):\n                # should not really happen\n                env = dict()\n                for env_item in value:\n                    _parse_env_kv(env_item, value[env_item])\n            else:\n                # at this point it should be a simple string, also should not happen\n                env = templar.template(value, convert_bare=False)\n\n        return env\n\n    def _post_validate_changed_when(self, attr, value, templar):\n        '''\n        changed_when is evaluated after the execution of the task is complete,\n        and should not be templated during the regular post_validate step.\n        '''\n        return value\n\n    def _post_validate_failed_when(self, attr, value, templar):\n        '''\n        failed_when is evaluated after the execution of the task is complete,\n        and should not be templated during the regular post_validate step.\n        '''\n        return value\n\n    def _post_validate_until(self, attr, value, templar):\n        '''\n        until is evaluated after the execution of the task is complete,\n        and should not be templated during the regular post_validate step.\n        '''\n        return value\n\n    def get_vars(self):\n        all_vars = dict()\n        if self._parent:\n            all_vars.update(self._parent.get_vars())\n\n        all_vars.update(self.vars)\n\n        if 'tags' in all_vars:\n            del all_vars['tags']\n        if 'when' in all_vars:\n            del all_vars['when']\n\n        return all_vars\n\n    def get_include_params(self):\n        all_vars = dict()\n        if self._parent:\n            all_vars.update(self._parent.get_include_params())\n        if self.action in C._ACTION_ALL_INCLUDES:\n            all_vars.update(self.vars)\n        return all_vars\n\n    def copy(self, exclude_parent=False, exclude_tasks=False):\n        new_me = super(Task, self).copy()\n\n        new_me._parent = None\n        if self._parent and not exclude_parent:\n            new_me._parent = self._parent.copy(exclude_tasks=exclude_tasks)\n\n        new_me._role = None\n        if self._role:\n            new_me._role = self._role\n\n        new_me.implicit = self.implicit\n        new_me.resolved_action = self.resolved_action\n\n        return new_me\n\n    def serialize(self):\n        data = super(Task, self).serialize()\n\n        if not self._squashed and not self._finalized:\n            if self._parent:\n                data['parent'] = self._parent.serialize()\n                data['parent_type'] = self._parent.__class__.__name__\n\n            if self._role:\n                data['role'] = self._role.serialize()\n\n            data['implicit'] = self.implicit\n            data['resolved_action'] = self.resolved_action\n\n        return data\n\n    def deserialize(self, data):\n\n        # import is here to avoid import loops\n        from ansible.playbook.task_include import TaskInclude\n        from ansible.playbook.handler_task_include import HandlerTaskInclude\n\n        parent_data = data.get('parent', None)\n        if parent_data:\n            parent_type = data.get('parent_type')\n            if parent_type == 'Block':\n                p = Block()\n            elif parent_type == 'TaskInclude':\n                p = TaskInclude()\n            elif parent_type == 'HandlerTaskInclude':\n                p = HandlerTaskInclude()\n            p.deserialize(parent_data)\n            self._parent = p\n            del data['parent']\n\n        role_data = data.get('role')\n        if role_data:\n            r = Role()\n            r.deserialize(role_data)\n            self._role = r\n            del data['role']\n\n        self.implicit = data.get('implicit', False)\n        self.resolved_action = data.get('resolved_action')\n\n        super(Task, self).deserialize(data)\n\n    def set_loader(self, loader):\n        '''\n        Sets the loader on this object and recursively on parent, child objects.\n        This is used primarily after the Task has been serialized/deserialized, which\n        does not preserve the loader.\n        '''\n\n        self._loader = loader\n\n        if self._parent:\n            self._parent.set_loader(loader)\n\n    def _get_parent_attribute(self, attr, extend=False, prepend=False):\n        '''\n        Generic logic to get the attribute or parent attribute for a task value.\n        '''\n\n        extend = self._valid_attrs[attr].extend\n        prepend = self._valid_attrs[attr].prepend\n        try:\n            value = self._attributes[attr]\n            # If parent is static, we can grab attrs from the parent\n            # otherwise, defer to the grandparent\n            if getattr(self._parent, 'statically_loaded', True):\n                _parent = self._parent\n            else:\n                _parent = self._parent._parent\n\n            if _parent and (value is Sentinel or extend):\n                if getattr(_parent, 'statically_loaded', True):\n                    # vars are always inheritable, other attributes might not be for the parent but still should be for other ancestors\n                    if attr != 'vars' and hasattr(_parent, '_get_parent_attribute'):\n                        parent_value = _parent._get_parent_attribute(attr)\n                    else:\n                        parent_value = _parent._attributes.get(attr, Sentinel)\n\n                    if extend:\n                        value = self._extend_value(value, parent_value, prepend)\n                    else:\n                        value = parent_value\n        except KeyError:\n            pass\n\n        return value\n\n    def all_parents_static(self):\n        if self._parent:\n            return self._parent.all_parents_static()\n        return True\n\n    def get_first_parent_include(self):\n        from ansible.playbook.task_include import TaskInclude\n        if self._parent:\n            if isinstance(self._parent, TaskInclude):\n                return self._parent\n            return self._parent.get_first_parent_include()\n        return None\n# Unit test for method get_first_parent_include of class Task\ndef              for k in env_item:\n                            _parse_env_kv(k, env_item[k])\n                    else:\n                        isdict = templar.template(env_item, convert_bare=False)\n environment value, skipping: %s\" % value)\n\n            elif isinstance(value, dict):\n                # should not really happen\n                env = dict()\n                for env_item in super(Task, self).copy()\n\n        new_me._parent = None\n        if self._parent and not exclude_parent:\n            new_me._parent = self._parent.copy(exclude_tasks=exclude_tasks)\n\n        new_me._role = None\n        if self._role:\n            new_me._role = self._role\n\n        new_me.implicit = self.implicit\n        new_me.resolved_action = self.resolved_action\n\n        return new_me\n\n    def serialize(self):\n        data = super(Task, self).serialize()\n\n        if not self._squashed and not self._finalized:\n            if self._parent:\n                data['parent'] = self._parent.serialize()\n                data['parent_type'] = self._parent.__class__.__name__\n\n            if self._role:\n                data['role'] = self._role.serialize()\n\n loops\n        from ansible.playbook.task_include import TaskInclude\n        from ansible.playbook.handler_task_include import HandlerTaskInclude\n\n        parent_data = data.get('parent', None)\n serialized/deserialized, which\n        does not preserve the loader.\n        '''\n\n        self._loader = loader\n\n        if self._parent:\n            self._parent.set_loader(loader)\n\n    def the parent\n            # otherwise, defer to the grandparent\n            if getattr(self._parent, 'statically_loaded', True):\n                _parent = self._parent\n            else:\n in ds:\n            # _load_vars is defined in Base, and is used to load a dictionary\n            # or list of dictionaries in a standard way\n            new_ds['vars'] = self._load_vars(None, ds.get('vars'))\n        else:\n            new_ds['vars'] = dict()\n\n        for (k, v) in iteritems(ds):\n            if k in ('action', 'local_action', 'args', 'delegate_to') or k == action or k == 'shell':\n                # we don't want to re-assign these values, which were determined by the ModuleArgsParser() above\n                continue\n            elif k.startswith('with_') and k.replace(\"with_\", \"\") in lookup_loader:\n                # transform into loop property\n                self._preprocess_with_loop(ds, new_ds, k, v)\n            elif C.INVALID_TASK_ATTRIBUTE_FAILED or k in self._valid_attrs:\n                new_ds[k] = v\n            else:\n                display.warning(\"Ignoring invalid attribute: %s\" % k)\n\n        return super(Task, self).preprocess_data(new_ds)\n\n    def _load_loop_control(self, attr, ds):\n        if not isinstance(ds, dict):\n            raise AnsibleParserError(\n                \"the `loop_control` value must be specified as a dictionary and cannot \"\n                \"be a variable itself (though it can contain variables)\",\n                obj=ds,\n            )\n\n        return LoopControl.load(data=ds, variable_manager=self._variable_manager, loader=self._loader)\n\n    def _validate_attributes(self, ds):\n        try:\n            super(Task, self)._validate_attributes(ds)\n        except AnsibleParserError as e:\n            e.message += '\\nThis error can be suppressed as a warning using the \"invalid_task_attribute_failed\" configuration'\n            raise e\n\n    def post_validate(self, templar):\n        '''\n        Override of base class post_validate, to also do final validation on\n        the block and task include (if any) to which this task belongs.\n        '''\n\n        if self._parent:\n            self._parent.post_validate(templar)\n\n        if AnsibleCollectionConfig.default_collection:\n            pass\n\n        super(Task, self).post_validate(templar)\n\n    def _post_validate_loop(self, attr, value, templar):\n        '''\n        Override post validation for the loop field, which is templated\n        specially in the TaskExecutor class when evaluating loops.\n        '''\n        return value\n\n    def _post_validate_environment(self, attr, value, templar):\n        '''\n        Override post validation of vars on the play, as we don't want to\n        template these too early.\n        '''\n        env = {}\n        if value is not None:\n\n            def _parse_env_kv(k, v):\n                try:\n                    env[k] = templar.template(v, convert_bare=False)\n                except AnsibleUndefinedVariable as e:\n                    error = to_native(e)\n                    if self.action in C._ACTION_FACT_GATHERING and 'ansible_facts.env' in error or 'ansible_env' in error:\n                        # ignore as fact gathering is required for 'env' facts\n                        return\n                    raise\n\n            if isinstance(value, list):\n                for env_item in value:\n                    if isinstance(env_item, dict):\n                        for k in env_item:\n                            _parse_env_kv(k, env_item[k])\n                    else:\n                        isdict = templar.template(env_item, convert_bare=False)\n                        if isinstance(isdict, dict):\n                            env.update(isdict)\n                        else:\n                            display.warning(\"could not parse environment value, skipping: %s\" % value)\n\n            elif isinstance(value, dict):\n                # should not really happen\n                env = dict()\n                for env_item in value:\n                    _parse_env_kv(env_item, value[env_item])\n            else:\n                # at this point it should be a simple string, also should not happen\n                env = templar.template(value, convert_bare=False)\n\n        return env\n\n    def _post_validate_changed_when(self, attr, value, templar):\n        '''\n        changed_when is evaluated after the execution of the task is complete,\n        and should not be templated during the regular post_validate step.\n        '''\n        return value\n\n    def _post_validate_failed_when(self, attr, value, templar):\n        '''\n        failed_when is evaluated after the execution of the task is complete,\n        and should not be templated during the regular post_validate step.\n        '''\n        return value\n\n    def _post_validate_until(self, attr, value, templar):\n        '''\n        until is evaluated after the execution of the task is complete,\n        and should not be templated during the regular post_validate step.\n        '''\n        return value\n\n    def get_vars(self):\n        all_vars = dict()\n        if self._parent:\n            all_vars.update(self._parent.get_vars())\n\n        all_vars.update(self.vars)\n\n        if 'tags' in all_vars:\n            del all_vars['tags']\n        if 'when' in all_vars:\n            del all_vars['when']\n\n        return all_vars\n\n    def get_include_params(self):\n        all_vars = dict()\n        if self._parent:\n            all_vars.update(self._parent.get_include_params())\n        if self.action in C._ACTION_ALL_INCLUDES:\n            all_vars.update(self.vars)\n        return all_vars\n\n    def copy(self, exclude_parent=False, exclude_tasks=False):\n        new_me = super(Task, self).copy()\n\n        new_me._parent = None\n        if self._parent and not exclude_parent:\n            new_me._parent = self._parent.copy(exclude_tasks=exclude_tasks)\n\n        new_me._role = None\n        if self._role:\n            new_me._role = self._role\n\n        new_me.implicit = self.implicit\n        new_me.resolved_action = self.resolved_action\n\n        return new_me\n\n    def serialize(self):\n        data = super(Task, self).serialize()\n\n        if not self._squashed and not self._finalized:\n            if self._parent:\n                data['parent'] = self._parent.serialize()\n                data['parent_type'] = self._parent.__class__.__name__\n\n            if self._role:\n                data['role'] = self._role.serialize()\n\n            data['implicit'] = self.implicit\n            data['resolved_action'] = self.resolved_action\n\n        return data\n\n    def deserialize(self, data):\n\n        # import is here to avoid import loops\n        from ansible.playbook.task_include import TaskInclude\n        from ansible.playbook.handler_task_include import HandlerTaskInclude\n\n        parent_data = data.get('parent', None)\n        if parent_data:\n            parent_type = data.get('parent_type')\n            if parent_type == 'Block':\n                p = Block()\n            elif parent_type == 'TaskInclude':\n                p = TaskInclude()\n            elif parent_type == 'HandlerTaskInclude':\n                p = HandlerTaskInclude()\n            p.deserialize(parent_data)\n            self._parent = p\n            del data['parent']\n\n        role_data = data.get('role')\n        if role_data:\n            r = Role()\n            r.deserialize(role_data)\n            self._role = r\n            del data['role']\n\n        self.implicit = data.get('implicit', False)\n        self.resolved_action = data.get('resolved_action')\n\n        super(Task, self).deserialize(data)\n\n    def set_loader(self, loader):\n        '''\n        Sets the loader on this object and recursively on parent, child objects.\n        This is used primarily after the Task has been serialized/deserialized, which\n        does not preserve the loader.\n        '''\n\n        self._loader = loader\n\n        if self._parent:\n            self._parent.set_loader(loader)\n\n    def _get_parent_attribute(self, attr, extend=False, prepend=False):\n        '''\n        Generic logic to get the attribute or parent attribute for a task value.\n        '''\n\n        extend = self._valid_attrs[attr].extend\n        prepend = self._valid_attrs[attr].prepend\n        try:\n            value = self._attributes[attr]\n            # If parent is static, we can grab attrs from the parent\n            # otherwise, defer to the grandparent\n            if getattr(self._parent, 'statically_loaded', True):\n                _parent = self._parent\n            else:\n                _parent = self._parent._parent\n\n            if _parent and (value is Sentinel or extend):\n                if getattr(_parent, 'statically_loaded', True):\n                    # vars are always inheritable, other attributes might not be for the parent but still should be for other ancestors\n                    if attr != 'vars' and hasattr(_parent, '_get_parent_attribute'):\n                        parent_value = _parent._get_parent_attribute(attr)\n                    else:\n                        parent_value = _parent._attributes.get(attr, Sentinel)\n\n                    if extend:\n                        value = self._extend_value(value, parent_value, prepend)\n                    else:\n                        value = parent_value\n        except KeyError:\n            pass\n\n        return value\n\n    def all_parents_static(self):\n        if self._parent:\n            return self._parent.all_parents_static()\n        return True\n\n    def get_first_parent_include(self):\n        from ansible.playbook.task_include import TaskInclude\n        if self._parent:\n            if isinstance(self._parent, TaskInclude):\n                return self._parent\n            return self._parent.get_first_parent_include()\n        return None\n# Unit test for method preprocess_data of class Task\ndef test_Task_preprocess_data():"}], "max_tokens":                     return\n                    raise\n\n            if isinstance(value, list):\n                for env_item in value:\n                    if isinstance(env_item, dict):\n                        for k in env_item:\n                            _parse_env_kv(k, env_item[k])\n                    else:\n                        isdict = templar.template(env_item, convert_bare=False)\n environment value, skipping: %s\" % value)\n\n            elif isinstance(value, dict):\n                # should not really happen\n                env = dict()\n                for env_item in templar.template(value, convert_bare=False)\n\n        return env\n\n    def _post_validate_changed_when(self, attr, value, templar):\n        '''\n        changed_when is evaluated after the all_vars['when']\n\n        return all_vars\n\n    def get_include_params(self):\n        all_vars = dict()\n        if self._parent:\n            all_vars.update(self._parent.get_include_params())\n super(Task, self).copy()\n\n        new_me._parent = None\n        if self._parent and not exclude_parent:\n            new_me._parent = self._parent.copy(exclude_tasks=exclude_tasks)\n\n        new_me._role = None\n        if self._role:\n            new_me._role = self._role\n\n        new_me.implicit = self.implicit\n        new_me.resolved_action = self.resolved_action\n\n        return new_me\n\n    def serialize(self):\n        data = super(Task, self).serialize()\n\n        if not self._squashed and not self._finalized:\n            if self._parent:\n                data['parent'] = self._parent.serialize()\n                data['parent_type'] = self._parent.__class__.__name__\n\n            if self._role:\n                data['role'] = self._role.serialize()\n\n            data['implicit'] = self.implicit\n            data['resolved_action'] = self.resolved_action\n\n        return data\n\n    def deserialize(self, data):\n\n        # import is here to avoid import            args['_raw_params'] = args.pop('cmd')\n\n        new_ds['action'] = action\n        new_ds['args'] = args\n        new_ds['delegate_to'] = delegate_to\n\n        # we handle any 'vars' specified in the ds here, as we may\n        # be adding things to them below (special handling for includes).\n        # When that deprecated feature is removed, this can be too.\n        if 'vars' in ds:\n            # _load_vars is defined in Base, and is used to load a dictionary\n            # or list of dictionaries in a standard way\n            new_ds['vars'] = self._load_vars(None, ds.get('vars'))\n        else:\n            new_ds['vars'] = dict()\n\n        for (k, v) in iteritems(ds):\n            if k in ('action', 'local_action', 'args', 'delegate_to') or k == action or k == 'shell':\n                # we don't want to re-assign these values, which were determined by the ModuleArgsParser() above\n                continue\n            elif k.startswith('with_') and k.replace(\"with_\", \"\") in lookup_loader:\n                # transform into loop property\n                self._preprocess_with_loop(ds, new_ds, k, v)\n            elif C.INVALID_TASK_ATTRIBUTE_FAILED or k in self._valid_attrs:\n                new_ds[k] = v\n            else:\n                display.warning(\"Ignoring invalid attribute: %s\" % k)\n\n        return super(Task, self).preprocess_data(new_ds)\n\n    def _load_loop_control(self, attr, ds):\n        if not isinstance(ds, dict):\n            raise AnsibleParserError(\n                \"the `loop_control` value must be specified as a dictionary and cannot \"\n                \"be a variable itself (though it can contain variables)\",\n                obj=ds,\n            )\n\n        return LoopControl.load(data=ds, variable_manager=self._variable_manager, loader=self._loader)\n\n    def _validate_attributes(self, ds):\n        try:\n            super(Task, self)._validate_attributes(ds)\n        except AnsibleParserError as e:\n            e.message += '\\nThis error can be suppressed as a warning using the \"invalid_task_attribute_failed\" configuration'\n            raise e\n\n    def post_validate(self, templar):\n        '''\n        Override of base class post_validate, to also do final validation on\n        the block and task include (if any) to which this task belongs.\n        '''\n\n        if self._parent:\n            self._parent.post_validate(templar)\n\n        if AnsibleCollectionConfig.default_collection:\n            pass\n\n        super(Task, self).post_validate(templar)\n\n    def _post_validate_loop(self, attr, value, templar):\n        '''\n        Override post validation for the loop field, which is templated\n        specially in the TaskExecutor class when evaluating loops.\n        '''\n        return value\n\n    def _post_validate_environment(self, attr, value, templar):\n        '''\n        Override post validation of vars on the play, as we don't want to\n        template these too early.\n        '''\n        env = {}\n        if value is not None:\n\n            def _parse_env_kv(k, v):\n                try:\n                    env[k] = templar.template(v, convert_bare=False)\n                except AnsibleUndefinedVariable as e:\n                    error = to_native(e)\n                    if self.action in C._ACTION_FACT_GATHERING and 'ansible_facts.env' in error or 'ansible_env' in error:\n                        # ignore as fact gathering is required for 'env' facts\n                        return\n                    raise\n\n            if isinstance(value, list):\n                for env_item in value:\n                    if isinstance(env_item, dict):\n                        for k in env_item:\n                            _parse_env_kv(k, env_item[k])\n                    else:\n                        isdict = templar.template(env_item, convert_bare=False)\n                        if isinstance(isdict, dict):\n                            env.update(isdict)\n                        else:\n                            display.warning(\"could not parse environment value, skipping: %s\" % value)\n\n            elif isinstance(value, dict):\n                # should not really happen\n                env = dict()\n                for env_item in value:\n                    _parse_env_kv(env_item, value[env_item])\n            else:\n                # at this point it should be a simple string, also should not happen\n                env = templar.template(value, convert_bare=False)\n\n        return env\n\n    def _post_validate_changed_when(self, attr, value, templar):\n        '''\n        changed_when is evaluated after the execution of the task is complete,\n        and should not be templated during the regular post_validate step.\n        '''\n        return value\n\n    def _post_validate_failed_when(self, attr, value, templar):\n        '''\n        failed_when is evaluated after the execution of the task is complete,\n        and should not be templated during the regular post_validate step.\n        '''\n        return value\n\n    def _post_validate_until(self, attr, value, templar):\n        '''\n        until is evaluated after the execution of the task is complete,\n        and should not be templated during the regular post_validate step.\n        '''\n        return value\n\n    def get_vars(self):\n        all_vars = dict()\n        if self._parent:\n            all_vars.update(self._parent.get_vars())\n\n        all_vars.update(self.vars)\n\n        if 'tags' in all_vars:\n            del all_vars['tags']\n        if 'when' in all_vars:\n            del all_vars['when']\n\n        return all_vars\n\n    def get_include_params(self):\n        all_vars = dict()\n        if self._parent:\n            all_vars.update(self._parent.get_include_params())\n        if self.action in C._ACTION_ALL_INCLUDES:\n            all_vars.update(self.vars)\n        return all_vars\n\n    def copy(self, exclude_parent=False, exclude_tasks=False):\n        new_me = super(Task, self).copy()\n\n        new_me._parent = None\n        if self._parent and not exclude_parent:\n            new_me._parent = self._parent.copy(exclude_tasks=exclude_tasks)\n\n        new_me._role = None\n        if self._role:\n            new_me._role = self._role\n\n        new_me.implicit = self.implicit\n        new_me.resolved_action = self.resolved_action\n\n        return new_me\n\n    def serialize(self):\n        data = super(Task, self).serialize()\n\n        if not self._squashed and not self._finalized:\n            if self._parent:\n                data['parent'] = self._parent.serialize()\n                data['parent_type'] = self._parent.__class__.__name__\n\n            if self._role:\n                data['role'] = self._role.serialize()\n\n            data['implicit'] = self.implicit\n            data['resolved_action'] = self.resolved_action\n\n        return data\n\n    def deserialize(self, data):\n\n        # import is here to avoid import loops\n        from ansible.playbook.task_include import TaskInclude\n        from ansible.playbook.handler_task_include import HandlerTaskInclude\n\n        parent_data = data.get('parent', None)\n        if parent_data:\n            parent_type = data.get('parent_type')\n            if parent_type == 'Block':\n                p = Block()\n            elif parent_type == 'TaskInclude':\n                p = TaskInclude()\n            elif parent_type == 'HandlerTaskInclude':\n                p = HandlerTaskInclude()\n            p.deserialize(parent_data)\n            self._parent = p\n            del data['parent']\n\n        role_data = data.get('role')\n        if role_data:\n            r = Role()\n            r.deserialize(role_data)\n            self._role = r\n            del data['role']\n\n        self.implicit = data.get('implicit', False)\n        self.resolved_action = data.get('resolved_action')\n\n        super(Task, self).deserialize(data)\n\n    def set_loader(self, loader):\n        '''\n        Sets the loader on this object and recursively on parent, child objects.\n        This is used primarily after the Task has been serialized/deserialized, which\n        does not preserve the loader.\n        '''\n\n        self._loader = loader\n\n        if self._parent:\n            self._parent.set_loader(loader)\n\n    def _get_parent_attribute(self, attr, extend=False, prepend=False):\n        '''\n        Generic logic to get the attribute or parent attribute for a task value.\n        '''\n\n        extend = self._valid_attrs[attr].extend\n        prepend = self._valid_attrs[attr].prepend\n        try:\n            value = self._attributes[attr]\n            # If parent is static, we can grab attrs from the parent\n            # otherwise, defer to the grandparent\n            if getattr(self._parent, 'statically_loaded', True):\n                _parent = self._parent\n            else:\n                _parent = self._parent._parent\n\n            if _parent and (value is Sentinel or extend):\n                if getattr(_parent, 'statically_loaded', True):\n                    # vars are always inheritable, other attributes might not be for the parent but still should be for other ancestors\n                    if attr != 'vars' and hasattr(_parent, '_get_parent_attribute'):\n                        parent_value = _parent._get_parent_attribute(attr)\n                    else:\n                        parent_value = _parent._attributes.get(attr, Sentinel)\n\n                    if extend:\n                        value = self._extend_value(value, parent_value, prepend)\n                    else:\n                        value = parent_value\n        except KeyError:\n            pass\n\n        return value\n\n    def all_parents_static(self):\n        if self._parent:\n            return self._parent.all_parents_static()\n        return True\n\n    def get_first_parent_include(self):\n        from ansible.playbook.task_include import TaskInclude\n        if self._parent:\n            if isinstance(self._parent, TaskInclude):\n                return self._parent\n            return self._parent.get_first_parent_include()\n        return None\n# Unit test for method get_first_parent_include of class Task\ndef v):\n                try:\n                    env[k] = templar.template(v, convert_bare=False)\n                except AnsibleUndefinedVariable as e:\n                    error = to_native(e)\n                    if self.action in C._ACTION_FACT_GATHERING and 'ansible_facts.env' in error or 'ansible_env' in error:\n                        # ignore as fact gathering is required for 'env' facts\n                        return\n                    raise\n\n            if isinstance(value, list):\n                for env_item in value:\n                    if isinstance(env_item, dict):\n                        for k in env_item:\n                            _parse_env_kv(k, env_item[k])\n                    else:\n                        isdict = templar.template(env_item, convert_bare=False)\n                        if isinstance(isdict, dict):\n                            env.update(isdict)\n                        else:\n                            display.warning(\"could not parse environment value, skipping: %s\" % value)\n\n            elif isinstance(value, dict):\n                # should not really happen\n                env = dict()\n                for env_item in value:\n                    _parse_env_kv(env_item, value[env_item])\n            else:\n                # at this point it should be a simple string, also should not happen\n                env = templar.template(value, convert_bare=False)\n\n        return env\n\n    def _post_validate_changed_when(self, attr, value, templar):\n        '''\n        changed_when is evaluated after the execution of the task is complete,\n        and should not be templated during the regular post_validate step.\n        '''\n        return value\n\n    def _post_validate_failed_when(self, attr,       return value\n\n    def _post_validate_until(self, attr, value, templar):\n        '''\n        until is evaluated after the execution of the task is complete,\n        and should not be all_vars['when']\n\n        return all_vars\n\n    def get_include_params(self):\n        all_vars = dict()\n        if self._parent:\n            all_vars.update(self._parent.get_include_params())\n        if self.action in C._ACTION_ALL_INCLUDES:\n            all_vars.update(self.vars)\n        return all_vars\n\n    def copy(self, exclude_parent=False, exclude_tasks=False):\n        new_me = super(Task, self).copy()\n\n        new_me._parent = None\n        if self._parent and not exclude_parent:\n            new_me._parent = self._parent.copy(exclude_tasks=exclude_tasks)\n\n        new_me._role = None\n        if self._role:\n            new_me._role = self._role\n\n        new_me.implicit = self.implicit\n        new_me.resolved_action = self.resolved_action\n\n        return new_me\n\n    def serialize(self):\n        data = super(Task, self).serialize()\n\n        if not self._squashed and not self._finalized:\n            if self._parent:\n                data['parent'] = self._parent.serialize()\n                data['parent_type'] = self._parent.__class__.__name__\n\n            if self._role:\n                data['role'] = self._role.serialize()\n\n            data['implicit'] = self.implicit\n            data['resolved_action'] = self.resolved_action\n\n        return data\n\n    def deserialize(self, data):\n\n        # import is here to avoid import loops\n        from ansible.playbook.task_include import TaskInclude\n        from ansible.playbook.handler_task_include import HandlerTaskInclude\n\n        parent_data = data.get('parent', None)\n      p = TaskInclude()\n            elif parent_type == 'HandlerTaskInclude':\n                p = HandlerTaskInclude()\n            p.deserialize(parent_data)\n            self._parent = p\n serialized/deserialized, which\n        does not preserve the loader.\n        '''\n\n        self._loader = loader\n\n        if self._parent:\n            self._parent.set_loader(loader)\n\n    def  pass\n\n        return value\n\n    def all_parents_static(self):\n        if self._parent:\n            return self._parent.all_parents_static()\n        return True\n\n    def new_me._role = None\n        if self._role:\n            new_me._role = self._role\n\n        new_me.implicit = self.implicit\n        new_me.resolved_action = self.resolved_action\n\n        return new_me\n\n    def serialize(self):\n        data = super(Task, self).serialize()\n\n        if not self._squashed and not self._finalized:\n            if self._parent:\n                data['parent'] = self._parent.serialize()\n                data['parent_type'] = self._parent.__class__.__name__\n\n            if self._role:\n                data['role'] = self._role.serialize()\n\n            data['implicit'] = self.implicit\n            data['resolved_action'] = self.resolved_action\n\n        return data\n\n    def deserialize(self, data):\n\n        # import is here to avoid import loops\n        from ansible.playbook.task_include import TaskInclude\n        from ansible.playbook.handler_task_include import HandlerTaskInclude\n\n        parent_data = data.get('parent', None)\n        if parent_data:\n            parent_type = data.get('parent_type')\n            if parent_type == 'Block':\n                p = Block()\n            elif parent_type == 'TaskInclude':\n serialized/deserialized, which\n        does not preserve the loader.\n        '''\n\n        self._loader = loader\n\n        if self._parent:\n            self._parent.set_loader(loader)\n\n    def _get_parent_attribute(self, attr, extend=False, prepend=False):\n        '''\n        Generic logic to get the attribute or parent attribute for a task value.\n        '''\n\n        extend = self._valid_attrs[attr].extend\n        prepend = self._valid_attrs[attr].prepend\n        try:\n            value = self._attributes[attr]\n            # If parent is static, we can grab attrs from the parent\n            # otherwise, defer to the grandparent\n            if getattr(self._parent, 'statically_loaded', True):\n                _parent = self._parent\n            else:\n inheritable, other attributes might not be for the parent but still should be for other ancestors\n                    if attr != 'vars' and hasattr(_parent, '_get_parent_attribute'):\n                        parent_value = _parent._get_parent_attribute(attr)\n                    else:\n                        parent_value = _parent._attributes.get(attr, Sentinel)\n\n                    if extend:\n                        value = self._extend_value(value, parent_value, prepend)\n                    else:\n                        value = parent_value\n        except KeyError:\n            pass\n\n        return value\n\n    def all_parents_static(self):\n        if self._parent:\n            return self._parent.all_parents_static()\n        return True\n\n    def get_first_parent_include(self):\n        from ansible.playbook.task_include import TaskInclude\n        if self._parent:\n            if isinstance(self._parent, TaskInclude):\n                return v):\n                try:\n                    env[k] = templar.template(v, convert_bare=False)\n                except AnsibleUndefinedVariable as e:\n                    error = to_native(e)\n                     return\n                    raise\n\n            if isinstance(value, list):\n                for env_item in value:\n                    if isinstance(env_item, dict):\n new_me._role = None\n        if self._role:\n            new_me._role = self._role\n\n        new_me.implicit = self.implicit\n        new_me.resolved_action = self.resolved_action\n\n        return new_me\n\n    def serialize(self):\n        data = super(Task, self).serialize()\n\n        if not self._squashed and not self._finalized:\n            if self._parent:\n                data['parent'] AnsibleError(\"The 'cmd' argument cannot be used when other raw parameters are specified.\"\n                                       \" Please put everything in one or the other place.\", obj=ds)\n                args['_raw_params'] = args.pop('cmd')\n\n        new_ds['action'] = action\n        new_ds['args'] = args\n        new_ds['delegate_to'] = delegate_to\n\n        # we handle any 'vars' specified in the ds here, as we may\n        # be adding things to them below (special handling for includes).\n        # When that deprecated feature is removed, this can be too.\n        if 'vars' in ds:\n            # _load_vars is defined in Base, and is used to load a dictionary\n            # or list of dictionaries in a standard way\n            new_ds['vars'] = self._load_vars(None, ds.get('vars'))\n        else:\n            new_ds['vars'] = dict()\n\n        for (k, v) in iteritems(ds):\n            if k in ('action', 'local_action', 'args', 'delegate_to') or k == action or k == 'shell':\n                # we don't want to re-assign these values, which were determined by the ModuleArgsParser() above\n                continue\n            elif k.startswith('with_') and k.replace(\"with_\", \"\") in lookup_loader:\n                # transform into loop property\n                self._preprocess_with_loop(ds, new_ds, k, v)\n            elif C.INVALID_TASK_ATTRIBUTE_FAILED or k in self._valid_attrs:\n                new_ds[k] = v\n            else:\n                display.warning(\"Ignoring invalid attribute: %s\" % k)\n\n        return super(Task, self).preprocess_data(new_ds)\n\n    def _load_loop_control(self, attr, ds):\n        if not isinstance(ds, dict):\n            raise AnsibleParserError(\n                \"the `loop_control` value must be specified as a dictionary and cannot \"\n                \"be a variable itself (though it can contain variables)\",\n                obj=ds,\n            )\n\n        return LoopControl.load(data=ds, variable_manager=self._variable_manager, loader=self._loader)\n\n    def _validate_attributes(self, ds):\n        try:\n            super(Task, self)._validate_attributes(ds)\n        except AnsibleParserError as e:\n            e.message += '\\nThis error can be suppressed as a warning using the \"invalid_task_attribute_failed\" configuration'\n            raise e\n\n    def post_validate(self, templar):\n        '''\n        Override of base class post_validate, to also do final validation on\n        the block and task include (if any) to which this task belongs.\n        '''\n\n        if self._parent:\n            self._parent.post_validate(templar)\n\n        if AnsibleCollectionConfig.default_collection:\n            pass\n\n        super(Task, self).post_validate(templar)\n\n    def _post_validate_loop(self, attr, value, templar):\n        '''\n        Override post validation for the loop field, which is templated\n        specially in the TaskExecutor class when evaluating loops.\n        '''\n        return value\n\n    def _post_validate_environment(self, attr, value, templar):\n        '''\n        Override post validation of vars on the play, as we don't want to\n        template these too early.\n        '''\n        env = {}\n        if value is not None:\n\n            def _parse_env_kv(k, v):\n                try:\n                    env[k] = templar.template(v, convert_bare=False)\n                except AnsibleUndefinedVariable as e:\n                    error = to_native(e)\n                    if self.action in C._ACTION_FACT_GATHERING and 'ansible_facts.env' in error or 'ansible_env' in error:\n                        # ignore as fact gathering is required for 'env' facts\n                        return\n                    raise\n\n            if isinstance(value, list):\n                for env_item in value:\n                    if isinstance(env_item, dict):\n                        for k in env_item:\n                            _parse_env_kv(k, env_item[k])\n                    else:\n                        isdict = templar.template(env_item, convert_bare=False)\n                        if isinstance(isdict, dict):\n                            env.update(isdict)\n                        else:\n                            display.warning(\"could not parse environment value, skipping: %s\" % value)\n\n            elif isinstance(value, dict):\n                # should not really happen\n                env = dict()\n                for env_item in value:\n                    _parse_env_kv(env_item, value[env_item])\n            else:\n                # at this point it should be a simple string, also should not happen\n                env = templar.template(value, convert_bare=False)\n\n        return env\n\n    def _post_validate_changed_when(self, attr, value, templar):\n        '''\n        changed_when is evaluated after the execution of the task is complete,\n        and should not be templated during the regular post_validate step.\n        '''\n        return value\n\n    def _post_validate_failed_when(self, attr, value, templar):\n        '''\n        failed_when is evaluated after the execution of the task is complete,\n        and should not be templated during the regular post_validate step.\n        '''\n        return value\n\n    def _post_validate_until(self, attr, value, templar):\n        '''\n        until is evaluated after the execution of the task is complete,\n        and should not be templated during the regular post_validate step.\n        '''\n        return value\n\n    def get_vars(self):\n        all_vars = dict()\n        if self._parent:\n            all_vars.update(self._parent.get_vars())\n\n        all_vars.update(self.vars)\n\n        if 'tags' in all_vars:\n            del all_vars['tags']\n        if 'when' in all_vars:\n            del all_vars['when']\n\n        return all_vars\n\n    def get_include_params(self):\n        all_vars = dict()\n        if self._parent:\n            all_vars.update(self._parent.get_include_params())\n        if self.action in C._ACTION_ALL_INCLUDES:\n            all_vars.update(self.vars)\n        return all_vars\n\n    def copy(self, exclude_parent=False, exclude_tasks=False):\n        new_me = super(Task, self).copy()\n\n        new_me._parent = None\n        if self._parent and not exclude_parent:\n            new_me._parent = self._parent.copy(exclude_tasks=exclude_tasks)\n\n        new_me._role = None\n        if self._role:\n            new_me._role = self._role\n\n        new_me.implicit = self.implicit\n        new_me.resolved_action = self.resolved_action\n\n        return new_me\n\n    def serialize(self):\n        data = super(Task, self).serialize()\n\n        if not self._squashed and not self._finalized:\n            if self._parent:\n                data['parent'] = self._parent.serialize()\n                data['parent_type'] = self._parent.__class__.__name__\n\n            if self._role:\n                data['role'] = self._role.serialize()\n\n            data['implicit'] = self.implicit\n            data['resolved_action'] = self.resolved_action\n\n        return data\n\n    def deserialize(self, data):\n\n        # import is here to avoid import loops\n        from ansible.playbook.task_include import TaskInclude\n        from ansible.playbook.handler_task_include import HandlerTaskInclude\n\n        parent_data = data.get('parent', None)\n        if parent_data:\n            parent_type = data.get('parent_type')\n            if parent_type == 'Block':\n                p = Block()\n            elif parent_type == 'TaskInclude':\n                p = TaskInclude()\n            elif parent_type == 'HandlerTaskInclude':\n                p = HandlerTaskInclude()\n            p.deserialize(parent_data)\n            self._parent = p\n            del data['parent']\n\n        role_data = data.get('role')\n        if role_data:\n            r = Role()\n            r.deserialize(role_data)\n            self._role = r\n            del data['role']\n\n        self.implicit = data.get('implicit', False)\n        self.resolved_action = data.get('resolved_action')\n\n        super(Task, self).deserialize(data)\n\n    def set_loader(self, loader):\n        '''\n        Sets the loader on this object and recursively on parent, child objects.\n        This is used primarily after the Task has been serialized/deserialized, which\n        does not preserve the loader.\n        '''\n\n        self._loader = loader\n\n        if self._parent:\n            self._parent.set_loader(loader)\n\n    def _get_parent_attribute(self, attr, extend=False, prepend=False):\n        '''\n        Generic logic to get the attribute or parent attribute for a task value.\n        '''\n\n        extend = self._valid_attrs[attr].extend\n        prepend = self._valid_attrs[attr].prepend\n        try:\n            value = self._attributes[attr]\n            # If parent is static, we can grab attrs from the parent\n            # otherwise, defer to the grandparent\n            if getattr(self._parent, 'statically_loaded', True):\n                _parent = self._parent\n            else:\n                _parent = self._parent._parent\n\n            if _parent and (value is Sentinel or extend):\n                if getattr(_parent, 'statically_loaded', True):\n                    # vars are always inheritable, other attributes might not be for the parent but still should be for other ancestors\n                    if attr != 'vars' and hasattr(_parent, '_get_parent_attribute'):\n                        parent_value = _parent._get_parent_attribute(attr)\n                    else:\n                        parent_value = _parent._attributes.get(attr, Sentinel)\n\n                    if extend:\n                        value = self._extend_value(value, parent_value, prepend)\n                    else:\n                        value = parent_value\n        except KeyError:\n            pass\n\n        return value\n\n    def all_parents_static(self):\n        if self._parent:\n            return self._parent.all_parents_static()\n        return True\n\n    def get_first_parent_include(self):\n        from ansible.playbook.task_include import TaskInclude\n        if self._parent:\n            if isinstance(self._parent, TaskInclude):\n                return self._parent\n            return self._parent.get_first_parent_include()\n        return None\n# Unit test for method get_vars of class Task\ndef test_Task_get_vars():"}], "max_tokens": 200,  Override post validation of vars on the play, as we don't want to\n        template these too early.\n        '''\n        env = {}\n        if value is not None:\n\n            def _parse_env_kv(k, v):\n                try:\n                    env[k] = templar.template(v, convert_bare=False)\n                except AnsibleUndefinedVariable as e:\n                    error = to_native(e)\n                    if self.action in C._ACTION_FACT_GATHERING and 'ansible_facts.env' in error or 'ansible_env' in error:\n                        # ignore as fact gathering is required for 'env' facts\n                        return\n                    raise\n\n            if isinstance(value, list):\n                for env_item in value:\n                    if isinstance(env_item, dict):\n                        for k in env_item:\n                            _parse_env_kv(k, env_item[k])\n                    else:\n                        isdict = templar.template(env_item, convert_bare=False)\n                        if isinstance(isdict, dict):\n                            env.update(isdict)\n                        else:\n                            display.warning(\"could not parse environment value, skipping: %s\" % value)\n\n            elif isinstance(value, dict):\n                # should not really happen\n                env = dict()\n                for env_item in value:\n                    _parse_env_kv(env_item, value[env_item])\n            else:\n                # at this point it should be a simple string, also should not happen\n                env = templar.template(value, convert_bare=False)\n\n        return env\n\n    def _post_validate_changed_when(self, attr, value, templar):\n        '''\n        changed_when is evaluated after the execution of the task is complete,\n        and should not be templated during the regular post_validate step.\n        '''\n        return value\n\n    def _post_validate_failed_when(self, attr, all_vars['when']\n\n        return all_vars\n\n    def get_include_params(self):\n        all_vars = dict()\n        if self._parent:\n            all_vars.update(self._parent.get_include_params())\n super(Task, self).copy()\n\n        new_me._parent = None\n        if self._parent and not exclude_parent:\n            new_me._parent = self._parent.copy(exclude_tasks=exclude_tasks)\n\n        new_me._role = None\n        if self._role:\n            new_me._role = self._role\n\n        new_me.implicit = self.implicit\n        new_me.resolved_action = self.resolved_action\n\n        return new_me\n\n    def serialize(self):\n        data = super(Task, self).serialize()\n\n        if not self._squashed and not self._finalized:\n            if self._parent:\n                data['parent'] = self._parent.serialize()\n                data['parent_type'] = self._parent.__class__.__name__\n\n            if self._role:\n                data['role'] = self._role.serialize()\n\n            data['implicit'] = self.implicit\n            data['resolved_action'] = self.resolved_action\n\n        return data\n\n    def deserialize(self, data):\n\n        # import is here to avoid import loops\n        from ansible.playbook.task_include import TaskInclude\n        from ansible.playbook.handler_task_include import HandlerTaskInclude\n\n        parent_data = data.get('parent', None)\n serialized/deserialized, which\n        does not preserve the loader.\n        '''\n\n        self._loader = loader\n\n        if self._parent:\n            self._parent.set_loader(loader)\n\n    def new_me._role = None\n        if self._role:\n            new_me._role = self._role\n\n        new_me.implicit = self.implicit\n        new_me.resolved_action = self.resolved_action\n\n        return  Override post validation of vars on the play, as we don't want to\n        template these too early.\n        '''\n        env = {}\n        if value is not None:\n\n            def _parse_env_kv(k, v):\n                try:\n                    env[k] = templar.template(v, convert_bare=False)\n                except AnsibleUndefinedVariable as e:\n                    error = to_native(e)\n new_me\n\n    def serialize(self):\n        data = super(Task, self).serialize()\n\n        if not self._squashed and not self._finalized:\n            if self._parent:\n                data['parent']
